      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "261b930a93db70d4",
      "text": "I think the two words that spell the main trouble for this plan are &quot;browsing history.&quot; Most people are quite sensitive about this and assume it is private. Even if shared with Google for enhanced services, they don't really want advertisers to know anything about it."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2fd42a5c929a8969",
      "text": "Hell, even I feel an emotional punch when I think about advertisers being handed information about my browsing, no matter how carefully categorized, anonymized, and sanitized. And I know how this stuff actually works. I even agree that in theory it's better than the status quo with third party cookies, etc."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "451a6fecb7a0176d",
      "text": "Is this really going to fly in the long run? It seems unlikely as currently defined. Most people aren't going to understand it, just like they don't understand that Google doesn't sell user data to advertisers&#8212;a widely held false belief that Google has never really been able to dispel. And Privacy Sandbox is even more complicated to explain to the average nontechnical person."
    },
